{
  "stem": "10572.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went to his study and saw him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he sat me down in his book-lined library and said to me, you know, you cannot leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Your parents should not leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We have to keep the balance between evil and good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if all of you leave, we are left with evil and the majority has to be-- has to be a majority of good people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he tried to use his influence to encourage our staying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1936.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And let me say that in-- in-- after-- after Buchenwald, he asked me again to come and see him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I sat in his book-lined study, and he said to me this time, Fritz, I was all wrong.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Get out, and get out as fast as you can while you still can.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he asked me would I tell him some of the details of what I had seen in the concentration camp?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And even though I had signed all kinds of papers before I left Buchenwald-- I'm jumping a little bit ahead of my story-- that I would never talk about what I had seen there, I sat there with Dr.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Agermussen and told him every little detail about what I had experienced.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after I was all through, he looked at me and said, the reason that I was interested in this, I have the feeling that some day I will go to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And indeed he did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- in--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they would say to you, look, the old cliche, we don't mean you, but there are certainly some Jews who have done things that were wrong and you have to suffer.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Being innocent, you have to suffer with the ones who are-- who have been guilty.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
